<h2>Why Surplus Funds Often Go Unclaimed</h2>

<p>
Many surplus funds remain unclaimed due to lack of awareness or because homeowners never receive required notices after a sale. These funds may also be held by trustees, county treasurers, or courts until a claim is filed. :contentReference[oaicite:10]{index=10}
</p>

<p>
In some counties, if a claim isn’t filed within a statutory period, the surplus can eventually be treated as unclaimed property and transferred to the state. :contentReference[oaicite:11]{index=11}
</p>

